request.description:
The HTTP PATCH request to update a patient's information is used to modify the details of a specific patient. The request should be made to the endpoint `{{local}}patient/update/7/` with the payload containing the updated information.

### Response

The response of this request can be represented as a JSON schema. The structure of the response will depend on the specific fields that are updated, and the API will return the modified patient information in the form of a JSON object.

body.raw:
{ 
        "call_script_text": "Good morning/afternoon, this is (NAME), and I am calling on behalf of Dr. Sarah Mitchell's office. How are you today?

You had a visit with Dr. Sarah Mitchell on March 15, 2025. (Pause for any response) He/She has deemed it necessary due to your snoring, sleep disruption, daytime fatigue to order a sleep study. Since sleep affects so much of our health, we want to make sure we get you set up and taken care of. Your insurance does cover your study and your responsibility for the test is $485.00.

[EXPLAIN INSURANCE BREAKDOWN HERE. USE THE QUOTE PROVIDED IN CHART.]

This test is done in the comfort of your own home and surroundings. I will set you up with a sleep coach that goes over everything from how to apply the equipment to any questions you have about the process. The machine is sent to you so it's easy to understand. The earliest I have available to allow time for the machine to get to you is (DATE AND TIME). If that day does not work for you, we can choose another day and time. What works best for you? (Allow for response)

Ok great, I have you set up that day and I can take your patient responsibility at this time.

[SELECT PAYMENT OPTION 1-4 BASED ON PATIENT RESPONSE]

[VERIFY PATIENT ADDRESS AND EMAIL]

(Tech's name) will be your Certified Sleep Coach. He/She will personally set you up and make sure everything is comfortable. He/She will be setting up the virtual meeting with instructions to be emailed to you on the day of your appointment. Please make sure to check your email before your appointment  if you don't see it in your inbox, be sure to look in your junk and spam folders!

Please wait until (Sleep Coach) calls you on (scheduled date and time) for your virtual appointment to open the box.

Also, we do have a 24-hour cancellation and rescheduling policy, so please make sure to jot down this appointment in your calendar. Do you have any questions for me?"

       }
